   International Partnerships

      NPOESS will work with international space agencies in Europe and Japan
      to create a complete, technologically advanced system to benefit all:
        * The European Organisation for the Exploitation of Meteorological
          Satellites (EUMETSAT)
             + Senior officials committed to establish and maintain an
               excellent relationship
                  o The Director of EUMETSAT invited to the NPOESS Senior
                    Users Advisory Group (SUAG) meetings
                  o The Assistant Administrator for Satellite and Information
                    Services invited to the EUMETSAT General Council meetings
             + Exchange information
                  o Increase understanding, provide formal/informal
                    communication path
                  o Minimize synchronization problems
             + Plan for futureinvited EUMETSAT to participate in the NPOESS
               IORD-2 worldwide review
             + Initiate studies to address various technical issues



        * National Space Development Agency of Japan (NASDA)
             + NASA/IPO Partnership study analyses of ground stations to
               support Polar-orbiting Missions
             + NASDA tour of the NOAA Command and Data Acquisition Station in
               Fairbanks, Alaska in May 2000
             + IPO members participate in the Globecomm Systems Inc. (GCOM)
               Ground Segment Working Group
             + Continued discussions on cooperative concepts of operations
               for ground stations with NASDA

                               acquisition schedule
